Text preprocessing is an important step in Natural Language Processing that prepares raw text data for analysis. Real-world text often contains punctuation marks, stop words, and different word forms that can make processing difficult. In this program, two paragraphs are taken as input and several preprocessing techniques are applied to clean the text. These techniques include removing punctuation marks, removing stop words, stemming, and lemmatization. The implementation is done using the NLTK library in Python, which provides tools for tokenizing text and transforming words into their root or base forms.
